# Security

## Read-only Cypher (critical for GraphRAG)

Text2Cypher lets the LLM generate Cypher from user text. Never trust it blindly:

- Connect the agent with a **dedicated read-only Neo4j role/user**.
- Run generated queries inside `session.execute_read(...)`.
- Reject any query containing write clauses before execution:

```python
WRITE = re.compile(r"\b(CREATE|MERGE|DELETE|SET|REMOVE|DROP|LOAD\s+CSV|CALL\s+\{)\b", re.I)
if WRITE.search(query):
    raise UnsafeCypherError(query)
```

## Secrets & auth

- Compare secrets with `hmac.compare_digest`, never `==`.
- Every non-public route requires an auth dependency (Supabase JWT). No unauthenticated data/LLM endpoints.
- Never log secrets or PII; sanitize user-derived strings before logging.

## LLM calls

- Always pass `timeout=` and `max_tokens=` (read from settings). No unbounded calls.

## Transport & config

- CORS: explicit origin allowlist. Never `allow_origins=["*"]` with `allow_credentials=True`. Fail fast if origins unset in prod.
- Validate required env vars at startup; refuse to boot on missing/placeholder values.
- Global exception handler returns a generic body (`{"detail": "Internal server error"}`) + a `request_id`; never return `str(exc)`.
